-- Bayer Says Rice Fungicide Developed With Sumitomo Gets Approval in Japan
-- Mike Gavin
-- 2010-07-15T09:54:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/bayer-says-rice-fungicide-developed-with-sumitomo-gets-approval-in-japan.html

          
          
             Bayer AG said the new rice fungicide
isotianil has been granted regulatory approval in Japan, and a
market launch in that country is scheduled for next year.
Isotianil was jointly developed with Sumitomo Chemical,
specifically to be used in Japan to combat the plant disease
rice blast, Bayer said in an e-mailed statement today.  
          
          


  


        